		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You can use a bonus action to place a curse on a creature you can see within 30ft. The curse lasts 1 minute, ending early if the creature dies, you die, or you become incapacitated.</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">When you deal damage against the cursed creature, it takes an additional 1d4 Necrotic damage. This bonus increases by 1d4 at 10th level, and again at 15th and 19th level.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You gain a pool of necrosis dice, which begins empty. When the cursed creature fails a saving throw, add one necrosis die to this pool. You can spend a necrosis die whenever you deal damage with your Eldritch Blast, or a spell of 1st level or higher that deals necrotic damage, to deal an additional 1d4 necrotic damage. The pool disappears when you finish a short or long rest.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you have used this feature, you can&rsquo;t use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
